<Window x:Class="ZooSimulator.View.GuideWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:ZooSimulator.View"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Icon="{StaticResource QuestionMark}"
        ResizeMode="NoResize"
        
        Title="Guide" Height="500" Width="450">
    <FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
        <FlowDocument FontFamily="Calibri">
            <Paragraph FontSize="30" Margin="0">How to Play:</Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="10">
                The application shows three cages containing three different types of animal: monkey, giraffe and elephant. 
                Each cage contains five animals for each group.
                Every hour each animal loses between 0% and 20% of their current health.
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph  Margin="10">
                If the User feeds the animals (by pressing the
                <Bold>Feed</Bold> button), each group of animals will receive a health boost ranging from 10%
                to 25% of their current health.
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph Margin="10">
                Keep in mind that:
            </Paragraph>
            
            <List MarkerStyle="Disc">
                <ListItem Margin="10">
                    <Paragraph>
                        To see an animal to walk (or to move around) just click on it.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem Margin="10">
                    <Paragraph>
                        When an Elephant has a health below 70% it cannot walk.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem Margin="10">
                    <Paragraph>
                        If an Elephant health does not return above 70% once the subsequent hour has
                        elapsed, it is pronounced dead. During this interval it will enter the Dying Stage. If the User feeds it in time, the Elephant might survive.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph Margin="10">
                        When a Monkey has a health below 30%, it is pronounced dead straight away.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph Margin="10">
                        When a Giraffe has a health below 50%, it is pronounced dead straight away
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph Margin="10">
                        Dead Animals will be removed from the screen thanks to the Zoo's HealthMonitorService class.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
            </List>

            <Paragraph Margin="10">
                Also, the User can skip the one hour of waiting time by pressing the
                <Bold>"1 Hour Jump"</Bold> button. This will automatically decrease the Animal's health.
                After that, the program will resume its execution as normal waiting for the next hourt to pass before decreasing the animal's health.
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
                Have Fun!
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
                Salvatore Amaddio.
            </Paragraph>
        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
</Window>
